POLS 3360 - Classical Foundations of Western Political
Theory
Examines the foundations of Western political theory from ancient
Greece through the Roman Empire. The course will trace the
development of Western political ideas and the accompanying
vocabulary through Greek theater, the Pre-Socratics, Thucydides, Plato,
Aristotle, the Graeco-Roman philosophers, and Cicero.
Prerequisite: POLS 2305 and 2306.
